1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson we will explore adding and customizing a category template.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
In the previous lesson we learnt all about the various templates available.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,000
And we mentioned that the All Archives template is the default template WordPress uses to display smaller groupings of posts,

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,000
such as categories, tags, authors, dates, etc.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Please note I am using the Twenty Twenty-Four default theme.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
When we scroll down we will see how the All Archives template is currently structured,

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
and how posts within an archive will appear on the front end.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
When I visit one of my blog posts and click on the relevant category in this case Art,

9
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
I will be able to view all my posts labeled with the Art category.

10
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
And of course as you can see, the structure for this page has been dictated by the All Archives template.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
And as mentioned, all other categories and groupings of archives will display in the same way,

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
due to the fact that they have been assigned to the All Archives template.

13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
This is where creating a custom category template comes into play.

14
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Instead of using the generic archive template, you can design a template that suits your specific needs.

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Let's see this in action.

16
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
I am going to go ahead and add a category template to change the display of posts within the Art category.

17
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
So I will make my way to templates and click on the plus icon or the Inserter next to templates.

18
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
And then I will add a category archives template.

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Now you have two choices.

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Firstly, you can create a single template for all your categories.

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Or you may decide to create a template for each specific category.

22
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
I am going to select the second option as I want to create a specific template for the Art category.

23
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Once selected, I will be able to choose a pattern that comes with the Twenty Twenty-Four theme.

24
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
But I will go ahead and select Skip to start blank.

25
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Now I can start building my blank template.

26
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
And the first thing I will add is my new header.

27
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
A header which I have already created and named Art Header.

28
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Once the unique header has been added to the template, I can click on the three vertical dots and select Add After.

29
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
And now we are going to add the Query Loop block.

30
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
And in this case, it will display all the Art posts.

31
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Now we can go ahead and select a pattern for how we want the posts to display.

32
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,000
And once the pattern has been added, we can modify it even further.

33
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
So let's go ahead and open up the List view.

34
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
And then look at all the nested blocks within the Query Loop block.

35
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
We are after the Post Template block.

36
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:13,000
When we select the Post Template block, we will see we have three columns.

37
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
And we can change that to four.

38
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
But in this example, we will settle for two columns.

39
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Next, I want to delete my Post Excerpt block.

40
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,000
So click on one of the posts, select the Post Excerpt block, click on the three vertical dots, and scroll down to the bottom and select Delete.

41
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Then I will select the Group block and add some more padding around the content.

42
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
So I'll open up my Styles, go to padding and add some more padding on the left and right.

43
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
You are welcome to make further modifications, but for this example, I am done.

44
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
So the next step is to add a footer.

45
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,000
And I am just going to add the general footer that I've used on my other templates as well.

46
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Now we can go ahead and see what our Art category will look like from the front end.

47
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
So if we select the relevant category now, namely Art, we will see the archives page for the Art category, with a unique header and modified content layout.

48
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
And this was of course achieved by adding and changing a category template for a specific item.

49
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
And if you wanted to go ahead and create a new template for a different category, you can click on the plus icon, next to templates, select category archives and then a category for a specific item.

50
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
And then I can create a unique template for my lifestyle category or for my sports category, for example.

51
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,000
I trust you now feel comfortable adding a category template for all categories or a specific category.

